    <article id="main-content" class="article">
      <header class="article-header">
        <h1 title="How to Report Bugs and Feedback in C4 PTR" class="article-title">
          How to Report Bugs and Feedback in C4 PTR
          
        </h1>

        <div class="article-author">
          
          <div class="article-meta">
            

            <div class="meta-group">
              
                <span class="meta-data"><time datetime="2026-06-02T19:53:35Z" title="2026-06-02T19:53:35Z" data-datetime="relative">June 02, 2026 19:53</time></span>
                <span class="meta-data">Updated</span>
              
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        
          <div class="article-subscribe"><div data-helper="subscribe" data-json="{&quot;item&quot;:&quot;article&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/hc/en-us/articles/52250104058131-How-to-Report-Bugs-and-Feedback-in-C4-PTR/subscription.json&quot;,&quot;follow_label&quot;:&quot;Follow&quot;,&quot;unfollow_label&quot;:&quot;Unfollow&quot;,&quot;following_label&quot;:&quot;Following&quot;,&quot;can_subscribe&quot;:true,&quot;is_subscribed&quot;:false}"></div></div>
        
      </header>

      <section class="article-info">
        <div class="article-content">
          <div class="article-body"><p>C4 PTR is a test environment, which means you may encounter bugs, unfinished systems, or features that change over time.</p><p>If you find an issue or want to share feedback, please use the in-game support menu so the team can review reports in the right place.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4QHZG8QBHJN9H2Y3W1M22K">Open the support menu</h2><p>From the main map, click the <strong>orange bug icon</strong>.<img src="/hc/article_attachments/52250136097939" width="800" height="141"></p><p>This opens the C4 PTR support menu.<img src="/hc/article_attachments/52250136098451" width="1392" height="648"></p><p>From this menu, you can access support and feedback options, including:</p><ul>
<li data-list-item-id="e8b2b91148d4e4267ad318468cca72238">Knowledge Base</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e0fc8d530b38f009a4a5daed6f13ef87f">Community Reports Dashboard</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e548e75ffe089636d75340925ba6811d6">Bug reporting</li>
<li data-list-item-id="effa696829866a97728f366109ea08c33">Feedback and suggestions</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e5763b5d8a825e465f2206793a9e9c01d">Feature requests</li>
<li data-list-item-id="eb7b7a0ef312ee165a37140dbec7c3667">Ticket creation</li>
</ul><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4QJ3KBR3J0ZR3CDAGGKTPN">Before submitting a report</h2><p>Before creating a new bug report or feedback entry, check the <a href="https://nsim.app.n8n.cloud/webhook/c4-public-reports"><strong>Community Reports Dashboard</strong></a>.</p><p>Another player may have already reported the same issue or suggested the same improvement.</p><p>If your issue already exists, you can upvote the existing report instead of creating a duplicate.</p><p>This helps the team understand which issues are affecting more players.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4QJBBQVS5FBM5JGTY36DVB">When to submit a bug report</h2><p>Submit a bug report when something is not working as expected.</p><p>Examples include:</p><ul>
<li data-list-item-id="e3468fdb26a464fd30a3b6bdca4dd2a2e">A transaction failed or did not complete correctly.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ee62118115dc68886b4b89cf9244e8f27">A button does not respond.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ee38fa8e0dc2a8a3a22023cca04426943">A menu does not open.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e0676455c6c1d8dda6ebcb0fcde13f27c">A fleet, resource, Claim Stake, or crafting action behaves incorrectly.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e7b89a1cd2b0d9f4ee8db7c8478ce5f3a">You receive an error message.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ece4f4e19809c0cc11aaa078dc9b6fde7">Something appears visually broken or missing.</li>
</ul><p>When reporting a bug, try to include as much useful information as possible.</p><p>Helpful details include:</p><ul>
<li data-list-item-id="e29ece1ce9ac5c6c3d9894af7f7e2ab71">What you were trying to do</li>
<li data-list-item-id="eeb4fa9fe09627bb012696cdc4ae1bab8">What happened instead</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e59362e8458c1f14f51a975df2584c140">The steps needed to reproduce the issue</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e6d89d4d4bd0e013096c92c8b3a162b2d">Screenshots or error messages, if available</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e1e3666f6def996ac5e727de4c34ae165">Your browser and device information, if relevant</li>
</ul><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4QJFER0RXP0XA3RQKJ78XM">When to submit feedback or suggestions</h2><p>Submit feedback or suggestions when something works, but you think it could be improved.</p><p>Examples include:</p><ul>
<li data-list-item-id="e360255316ad82e88f02fa13ef436a2cc">A menu is confusing.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="eff3eaf9cbb9cdaae861a6a783e58fd80">A button or action is hard to find.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e36f605961e4241aa4305326af8cef7e7">A flow feels too slow or unclear.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e0f865c2db9cad3d635dd0ad70299745a">A tutorial, tooltip, or explanation is missing.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e0732ee6f612053ad116c238e16b66757">A feature could be easier to understand.</li>
</ul><p>Feedback helps the team improve the player experience during PTR.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4QJPVNFM7ZYX8AWVM1R0TC">When to submit a feature request</h2><p>Submit a feature request when you want to suggest a new feature or functionality that does not currently exist.</p><p>Feature requests are different from bug reports. A bug report is for something broken, while a feature request is for something new or missing.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4QJTWYMWCJDR4RDA9P0EDQ">When to create a support ticket</h2><p>Create a support ticket if you need direct help from the support team.</p><p>Use this option when your issue requires personal support or account-specific investigation.</p><p>For general bugs, feedback, and feature requests, use the report and feedback tools first so the information can be tracked with other community reports.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4QJZMH3TCG78B0VA6A2DKQ">Why reporting matters</h2><p>The development team uses community reports to help track bugs and review feedback during PTR.</p><p>Using the support menu helps keep reports organized and makes it easier for the team to identify common issues, review player suggestions, and improve C4 PTR over time.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4QK5TAWQ6X34P5ABDAWG4A">Summary</h2><p>To report bugs or feedback in C4 PTR:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="e0f269629a837c1c005bf4b6fc7966d2f">Open the main map.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ea7f79cf4a4b51ecb3eb7282e904d12e1">Click the <strong>orange bug icon</strong>.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e3b9a92dd748b994801bbc6ba43663d3a">Check the <strong>Community Reports Dashboard</strong> first.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e60723354dfc7bbe63ca08960f2b13831">Upvote an existing report if your issue is already listed.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e78eb70c720e767d469f5e54c94ab586e">Submit a new bug report, feedback entry, feature request, or support ticket when needed.</li>
</ol></div>

          

          
        </div>
      </section>

